        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 3:40PM EDT by NWS Miami FL</headline>
        <description>Temperatures late this afternoon will be in the mid to upper 90s
over the metro areas of Palm Beach, Broward, and Miami-Dade
Counties. The relative humidity will be in the 40s to around 50.
This will allow for the heat index readings to get up to near 110
degrees for the next hour or two. People need to drink plenty of
water and take breaks inside from the heat.
</description>
